1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:02,070
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,140 --> 00:00:03,880
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,410 --> 00:00:07,350
(Episode 25)

4
00:00:08,380 --> 00:00:09,380
What?

5
00:00:10,180 --> 00:00:13,550
I'm losing my mind, seriously.
I'm just so happy.

6
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:18,520
What? Why are you laughing?

7
00:00:18,590 --> 00:00:21,130
What? Why can't I?

8
00:00:21,130 --> 00:00:22,860
You said you ran here
because you missed me.

9
00:00:23,130 --> 00:00:24,600
Am I not allowed to smile?

10
00:00:25,730 --> 00:00:28,030
Did you avoid calling me just
so you could hear me say that?

11
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:32,670
No, it's not that,
but I heard something.

12
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:36,240
I accidentally played hard to get.
My bad.

13
00:00:37,310 --> 00:00:40,210
- I owe Officer Jung for this.
- Officer Jung? Why bring him up?

14
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:42,080
What did Officer Jung say?

15
00:00:42,450 --> 00:00:43,450
Officer Jung?

16
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:51,460
"Don't let your loved one
become unhappy because of you."

17
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,790
"If you're not confident,"

18
00:00:55,060 --> 00:00:56,560
"then it's better
not to even start."

19
00:01:01,670 --> 00:01:02,900
Are you saying
you're not confident anymore?

20
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:06,370
No, that's not it.

21
00:01:07,510 --> 00:01:10,540
I was worried you'd waste your time
waiting for me...

22
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,280
if our brothers took a while
to reconcile.

23
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:16,650
That's what
I was a little worried about.

24
00:01:24,190 --> 00:01:25,190
I...

25
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,490
won't be wasting my time.

26
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:35,300
Let's just date in secret.

27
00:01:41,540 --> 00:01:42,540
Are you serious?

28
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:44,440
What? You don't want to?

29
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:46,080
No, it's not that.

30
00:01:48,050 --> 00:01:49,550
It's just... I have a question.

31
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:51,150
What is it?

32
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:53,850
So when did we
officially start dating?

33
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:59,120
Was it the day we went to the motel?
Or the day we kissed?

34
00:02:00,460 --> 00:02:03,760
Gosh, why does that even matter?
I'm leaving.

35
00:02:04,730 --> 00:02:06,260
Let go. I'm leaving.

36
00:02:06,260 --> 00:02:09,370
My gosh!
Hey, let go of me! I'm leaving!

37
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:12,770
- Hey, what's with you? Stop it.
- Dong Suk.

38
00:02:12,970 --> 00:02:15,910
- Ma'am, what's next?
- These three here.

39
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:20,880
What? Jeong Sun.

40
00:02:23,010 --> 00:02:24,980
You are Jeong Sun, right?

41
00:02:28,450 --> 00:02:29,450
Im Jeong Sun.

42
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:35,130
Hey, long time no see.

43
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:40,060
Wow, you look great.
I almost didn't recognize you.

44
00:02:40,830 --> 00:02:42,900
- Excuse me...
- After Jong Gil died,

45
00:02:43,170 --> 00:02:45,340
I was so worried about you.

46
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:50,070
So you had your daughter back then.

47
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:54,410
Hey, she looks just like you.
Has it really been that long?

48
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:58,580
Excuse me.
Look, you've got the wrong person.

49
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:02,290
Jeong Sun, it's me,
Hyeon Cheol, from...

50
00:03:02,350 --> 00:03:04,860
- The Seongwon Orphanage?
- Hey, listen to me!

51
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:07,430
I already told you, you're mistaken.

52
00:03:08,130 --> 00:03:10,830
My gosh. Hyeon Cheol, stop.

53
00:03:10,830 --> 00:03:12,630
- You're mistaken.
- No.

54
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:15,330
Gosh, how rude.

55
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:17,840
- Let's go.
- My gosh, I'm so sorry.

56
00:03:19,370 --> 00:03:20,570
I am so sorry.

57
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:22,770
Goodbye.

58
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:29,850
Here.

59
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:33,380
Try some.
It might not be from a master chef,

60
00:03:33,450 --> 00:03:34,520
but it should be pretty good.

61
00:03:34,950 --> 00:03:38,090
- You really didn't have to...
- I was craving some, too.

62
00:03:38,690 --> 00:03:42,260
- What's that smell?
- Father, it's tteokbokki. Join us.

63
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:45,600
- Let's keep this between us, okay?
- Of course.

64
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:48,700
Have a seat, Mr. Yang.

65
00:03:50,470 --> 00:03:53,940
Father,
you can only have three today.

66
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:57,910
- Why? I want more.
- I know it's delicious,

67
00:03:57,980 --> 00:04:02,310
but it's bad for your blood sugar.
Besides, you have a shoot tomorrow.

68
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:04,320
You have to look your best on TV.

69
00:04:05,050 --> 00:04:06,080
All right.

70
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:08,750
Have it with this fish cake soup.

71
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:17,230
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

72
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:21,700
The next question is for Dr. Gong.

73
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:25,040
Dr. Gong, what kind of friend
is Dr. Yang to you?

74
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,180
Well...

75
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:37,280
The word "friend" doesn't even begin
to cover what he is to me.

76
00:04:38,380 --> 00:04:42,120
I really can't explain
my life without him.

77
00:04:42,250 --> 00:04:43,590
That's how close we are.

78
00:04:44,820 --> 00:04:47,960
Dong Ik sees things differently
than I do,

79
00:04:48,130 --> 00:04:50,090
so I actually have a lot
to learn from him.

80
00:04:51,130 --> 00:04:55,930
Even when I'm convinced I'm right,
he makes me think twice.

81
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:59,940
I see. And for you, Dr. Yang,

82
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:01,770
I'm curious what kind of friend
Dr. Gong is to you.

83
00:05:02,270 --> 00:05:06,610
Well, Jeong Han...
He's my source of inspiration.

84
00:05:07,410 --> 00:05:09,550
My muse, if you will.

85
00:05:10,780 --> 00:05:13,280
You could say I'm the type
who looks for the quick answer,

86
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:16,590
while Jeong Han is the type
who looks for the right one.

87
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:19,590
And that difference is
what helped me grow.

88
00:05:20,490 --> 00:05:22,590
Wow, you two are so genuine.
This is great.

89
00:05:23,030 --> 00:05:25,530
So heartwarming.
This is great stuff.

90
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:30,540
All right, let's take five,
and then we'll interview the son.

91
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,640
- Okay.
- Yes.

92
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:35,670
- Great work, everyone.
- Yes.

93
00:05:40,980 --> 00:05:44,620
Hey, you should quit your clinic
and become an actor. Seriously.

94
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:48,690
- That performance was Oscar-worthy.
- Tell me about it.

95
00:05:49,090 --> 00:05:52,390
Your acting was so moving,
it brought out the best actor in me.

96
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:54,630
Hello, Dr. Gong.

97
00:05:55,060 --> 00:05:56,130
Oh, hi.

98
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:59,560
Why are you here? You didn't want
to be part of the shoot.

99
00:06:00,030 --> 00:06:02,730
Oh, Director Yang was coming down
for his interview,

100
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:05,940
so I hitched a ride.
I thought I'd watch your interview.

101
00:06:06,470 --> 00:06:07,970
Hey, Dad.

102
00:06:09,010 --> 00:06:12,140
I'm sorry about
what happened last time.

103
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:14,410
It's all right.

104
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:16,780
Hey, let's go.

105
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:20,850
Oh, no, Dad. You go ahead.
I need to talk to Director Yang...

106
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,520
about something after his interview.

107
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:26,820
(Onjeong Market)

108
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:30,060
- All right, I'm heading out.
- Okay, Dad. Take care.

109
00:06:34,370 --> 00:06:36,700
Gosh, I was on pins and needles.

110
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:39,340
Me too. My goodness,
putting on an act like that...

111
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,710
What if they slip up
in front of the cameras?

112
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:43,170
Unbelievable.

113
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:46,380
- Are you ready for your interview?
- You bet.

114
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:49,180
Let's just see how long
you can keep up that phony act.

115
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:51,850
I apologized to your daughter.
You should be more like her, jerk.

116
00:06:51,950 --> 00:06:52,980
- Out of the way! I'm first!
- No, I'm first!

117
00:06:53,050 --> 00:06:55,050
- Why should I move? You move, jerk!
- Oh, for crying out loud!

118
00:06:55,590 --> 00:06:57,890
- Must you fight about everything?
- Hey, what's your problem?

119
00:06:58,490 --> 00:07:02,260
Just because we're dating in secret
doesn't mean I won't make an effort.

120
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:05,130
I'll use this documentary shoot
as an opportunity...

121
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,700
to get our brothers to make up...

122
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:08,600
and get both our families' blessing.
I promise.

123
00:07:09,770 --> 00:07:12,300
- Okay.
- Yes.

124
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:17,640
Wow, it's all young people here.

125
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:20,010
So what?

126
00:07:20,380 --> 00:07:23,580
I'll take you to the best places.
Okay, Suk?

127
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:27,420
- Don't call me that.
- Why? You like Dorphini better?

128
00:07:27,490 --> 00:07:28,990
- I do.
- I see.

129
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:31,990
- Then what should I call you?
- Me?

130
00:07:34,930 --> 00:07:36,460
Oh, how about Tamin?

131
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:38,130
Tamin?

132
00:07:38,230 --> 00:07:41,630
Sounds like a K-pop idol's name.
Tamin. Do you know his last name?

133
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:43,230
- What is it?
- Vi.

134
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,300
Vitamin?

135
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:48,070
Oh, come on.

136
00:07:48,570 --> 00:07:51,910
<i>- You're my vitamin</i>
- Hey, be quiet.

137
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:55,780
<i>- You're my endorphin</i>
<i></i>- Quiet. People are staring.

138
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:57,280
Who's staring?
Nobody is staring at us.

139
00:07:57,280 --> 00:08:00,220
My gosh.
So many lovey-dovey couples here.

140
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:01,690
Gives me a toothache just watching.

141
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:07,890
About my dad and Dr. Yang...
Even though they bicker nonstop,

142
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:10,830
once the cameras are rolling,
they seem so genuine, right?

143
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,400
They both want to show
their parents,

144
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,770
who might watch "Human Theater,"

145
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:19,500
that they're doing well.

146
00:08:21,570 --> 00:08:25,740
Do you ever wonder
if your birth mother might watch it?

147
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:28,010
I do.

148
00:08:28,810 --> 00:08:32,420
I think that's why I was especially
nervous during the interview.

149
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:34,050
I want to show her...

150
00:08:34,650 --> 00:08:37,420
that I'm doing well, too.

151
00:08:46,530 --> 00:08:48,070
You're back from the restroom
so soon... My gosh!

152
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:50,670
Auntie?

153
00:08:51,570 --> 00:08:55,810
- Hello.
- Oh, hi. Hyun Bin...

154
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,610
Hey, Auntie,
what are you doing here?

155
00:08:57,940 --> 00:09:01,480
Oh, I just met up with a friend
after work.

156
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:05,220
So, what are you two doing here?

157
00:09:06,180 --> 00:09:08,790
Oh, we work at the same company,
remember?

158
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:12,920
I gave her a ride since I was coming
for the interview.

159
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:15,890
Yes, and I treated him to a meal
to thank him.

160
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:20,100
Thanks again for the ride, Director.
I'll see you at work tomorrow.

161
00:09:20,130 --> 00:09:24,600
- My car's that way. I'll walk you.
- Oh, okay.

162
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:26,340
- Yes.
- Sounds good.

163
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,810
- See you this weekend, Auntie.
- Okay...

164
00:09:29,910 --> 00:09:30,910
Oh, okay.

165
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:33,040
- Get home safe. Bye.
- Bye.

166
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:39,520
- Man, that was a close call.
- What was that?

167
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:41,420
My goodness, that was a close call.

168
00:09:41,950 --> 00:09:43,960
Why are those two always together?

169
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:48,030
- They're not dating, are they?
- What?

170
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:50,730
Don't even joke about
something so scary.

171
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,330
My Ju Ah has a boyfriend.

172
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,970
Those two, I swear...

173
00:09:57,570 --> 00:10:00,370
How's your part-time job?
Is it tough?

174
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:03,740
It's tiring, but it's fun.

175
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:08,950
You say that, but aren't you worried
about your grades?

176
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:10,310
No, not at all.

177
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:14,450
I'm more relaxed since letting go,
so I've cut back on my medication.

178
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:18,060
- I'm home.
- Oh, welcome back.

179
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:20,890
Try coming home earlier
for a change.

180
00:10:21,130 --> 00:10:22,260
Don't start.

181
00:10:23,430 --> 00:10:24,430
Were you on a date?

182
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:27,930
- Yes. I'm going to go rest.
- Okay.

183
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,070
Hey, take your laundry with you.

184
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:36,210
- Goodness. Why, that...
- Okay. Text me when you get there.

185
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:39,910
Hey! I told you, it's dangerous
to talk on the phone while driving.

186
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:41,010
My goodness!

187
00:10:42,050 --> 00:10:43,450
It's me, your grandma.

188
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,850
Grandma, please knock next time.

189
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:51,460
Why so jumpy? I know
you're on the phone with Jun Hyeok.

190
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:53,260
Yes, I guess so.

191
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:54,730
Here you go.

192
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:58,230
And where are they?
Any balled-up socks? Hand them over.

193
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:01,270
Grandma, seriously...
There aren't any.

194
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:06,340
- Break bad habits before you marry.
- Sorry.

195
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:09,110
- Get some rest.
- Okay.

196
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:11,640
- Go on, Grandma.
- Okay.

197
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:24,120
What? Your shift ended hours ago.
Why are you just getting home?

198
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:27,020
Did you sneak off on a date
and dump closing duties on us?

199
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,630
Yes, so what if I did?
What are you going to do about it?

200
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:32,200
You got to close up the restaurant
with Woo Jae, thanks to me.

201
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:34,500
I know. Thank you.

202
00:11:35,270 --> 00:11:37,030
- Where's Ji Hu?
- Tutoring.

203
00:11:38,170 --> 00:11:39,170
I'm done!

204
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:40,940
Finished!

205
00:11:41,140 --> 00:11:44,140
You worked hard, sweetie.
So? Is Min Seo a good tutor?

206
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:47,110
She's amazing. Just wait until
you see my midterm grades, Mom.

207
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:48,980
Really?

208
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:52,150
So cozy!

209
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:55,520
Nice. Very nice!

210
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:58,560
Want to see a photo
of your mom's shop?

211
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:00,360
Oh, right. You went there today.

212
00:12:00,930 --> 00:12:03,090
- So, how was it?
- Today?

213
00:12:03,530 --> 00:12:05,300
Please keep
what happened today a secret.

214
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,670
It was fun.

215
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:10,940
Oh, that's right.
Your mom made some tteokbokki.

216
00:12:10,940 --> 00:12:13,370
Let me guess. Grandpa whined
for a huge portion, didn't he?

217
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:14,710
He did.

218
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:23,210
Jeong Sun. You are Jeong Sun, right?

219
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:24,950
Im Jeong Sun.

220
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:29,520
After Jong Gil died,
I was so worried about you.

221
00:12:32,420 --> 00:12:33,420
- Hey.
- Oh, boy.

222
00:12:35,130 --> 00:12:36,190
Where's Hyun Bin?

223
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:38,800
Oh, he probably went home
after his interview.

224
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:41,130
He'll probably come on Saturday
when we film here.

225
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:45,800
When you were with him,
was he on the phone with anyone?

226
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:48,110
On the phone?
No, I don't think he was. Why?

227
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:51,710
Hyun Bin is seeing someone,
so I was wondering who it could be.

228
00:12:52,310 --> 00:12:54,810
Now that you mention it,
he brought...

229
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:57,050
Jeong Han's daughter that day
and again today.

230
00:12:57,680 --> 00:12:58,750
They probably just carpooled.

231
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:01,950
You don't think they're dating,
do you?

232
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:06,060
Please. Gong Ju Ah already brought
her boyfriend home to meet everyone.

233
00:13:07,420 --> 00:13:11,330
That must have bummed Hyun Bin out.
He used to have a crush on her.

234
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:14,800
Honey, that's ancient history.

235
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:19,570
You don't know what you're saying.
A man never forgets his first love.

236
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:25,380
I'm sorry.
I don't know what came over me.

237
00:13:25,710 --> 00:13:26,710
That was nonsense.

238
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,750
I'm just really stressed
from the shoot.

239
00:13:29,650 --> 00:13:31,520
Did your interview go well?

240
00:13:32,850 --> 00:13:36,690
It was flawless, absolutely perfect.
So you're up starting tomorrow.

241
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:38,660
So are you all prepared?

242
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:41,790
Honey...

243
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:43,430
Yes?

244
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:48,070
What if people from my past
recognize me when the show airs?

245
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:51,570
Come on, so what?
You didn't do anything wrong.

246
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:53,470
But still...

247
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:54,810
Why?

248
00:13:55,270 --> 00:13:58,310
Is it because you're afraid
people will find out your real name?

249
00:13:59,210 --> 00:14:01,750
Jeong Sun, how about a little kiss?

250
00:14:01,810 --> 00:14:04,980
Honey! I told you
not to call me that, didn't I?

251
00:14:05,580 --> 00:14:07,420
- Okay, Jeong Sun. My bad.
- My gosh.

252
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:12,060
Our Cha Se Ri is dripping
with class and style.

253
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:14,760
Who would possibly recognize you?
Don't worry!

254
00:14:15,690 --> 00:14:17,630
- You think so?
- Of course!

255
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:20,900
Oh, I'm tired.

256
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:37,250
When I ran your blood tests,
I also ran the tumor markers,

257
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:40,380
and the breast cancer markers
came back high.

258
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:52,530
What are you doing?

259
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:02,910
Why are you sleeping in the car
instead of going inside?

260
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,940
I wasn't sleeping. I was just
thinking about something.

261
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:09,610
- How was the shoot?
- Great, of course.

262
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:12,280
I think I'm a natural on camera,
don't you?

263
00:15:14,890 --> 00:15:18,120
- Hey.
- Should I practice my autograph?

264
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:20,760
What? What's wrong?

265
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:24,930
It's nothing. Let's just go inside.

266
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:29,900
- I just want to lie down.
- You should get a menopause test.

267
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:33,000
Always sleepy, wanting to lie down,
and constantly tired. Right?

268
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:35,010
You think I need a test
to know that?

269
00:15:35,670 --> 00:15:37,610
Stop stating the obvious.
Let's go inside.

270
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:41,880
See? That cranky tone is
a dead giveaway. Goodness.

271
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,480
All done.

272
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:50,450
Dad, are you nervous?

273
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:52,990
Nervous? What for?
I'll just act like I always do.

274
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:56,830
- You mean shouting and being angry?
- When do I ever do that?

275
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,560
See? There you go again,
getting angry.

276
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:01,470
What's taking Se Ri so long?

277
00:16:01,770 --> 00:16:03,200
It's a whole ordeal in there.

278
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:06,300
Oh, my goodness!

279
00:16:07,540 --> 00:16:08,540
Wow!

280
00:16:08,970 --> 00:16:10,070
What do you think? How do I look?

281
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,240
Ta-da!

282
00:16:13,140 --> 00:16:16,510
That is so extra.
It's way too much. Right?

283
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:21,890
- Why? Is it a little too much?
- Way too much!

284
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:25,860
Really? I bought this specifically
to wear for the shoot.

285
00:16:26,790 --> 00:16:30,560
How about this one? This flowy one.
This one. How about this?

286
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:31,960
Never!

287
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:36,730
Then what am I supposed to wear?
I think this one is pretty.

288
00:16:37,630 --> 00:16:38,640
Hey.

289
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,470
When filming at home, it's okay
to just be natural, right?

290
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:45,880
- Of course. That's our plan.
- Okay.

291
00:16:45,940 --> 00:16:48,280
I can already picture it.
The Yangs are going to go all out.

292
00:16:49,050 --> 00:16:52,950
They would, wouldn't they?
I bet they're preparing like crazy.

293
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,450
- By the way, Mother.
- Yes?

294
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:58,220
Is everything okay with Ju Ah?

295
00:16:58,660 --> 00:16:59,690
What do you mean?

296
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:03,460
At work, things seemed a bit off
between her and Jun Hyeok.

297
00:17:03,930 --> 00:17:07,100
No way. They were so lovey-dovey
on the phone yesterday.

298
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,030
I guess they made up.

299
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:11,240
That's a relief then.

300
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:15,310
Hey, you said Ju Ah is in charge
of the whole fashion show, right?

301
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:17,040
Yes.

302
00:17:17,340 --> 00:17:18,710
Just try to be understanding.

303
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:21,280
Her mom,
who was once against her career,

304
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:23,280
is now her model,
and she's running the show.

305
00:17:23,350 --> 00:17:24,720
Imagine how on edge she must be.

306
00:17:25,220 --> 00:17:29,290
Gosh, you always take Ju Ah's side
no matter what, Mother.

307
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:34,060
Hey, of course.
She's my granddaughter I raised.

308
00:17:35,890 --> 00:17:37,230
Must be nice to be Ju Ah.

309
00:17:43,830 --> 00:17:45,070
Hey, your turn to drive.

310
00:17:45,470 --> 00:17:50,170
Can you drive, Mom? I need to sleep.
Gosh, I didn't get a wink of sleep.

311
00:17:50,910 --> 00:17:52,340
Neither did I.

312
00:17:52,740 --> 00:17:55,680
Mom, I'm the creative director
for the fashion show.

313
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:59,620
I have a million things to do today,
so I can't afford to be out of it.

314
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:03,420
Hey, I'm the main model.
Doesn't my condition matter too?

315
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:04,560
Please.

316
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:19,440
Hey! Get the sleep out of your eyes
before Director Yang sees you. Okay?

317
00:18:19,940 --> 00:18:24,170
I didn't want Mom nagging about you,
so I pretended to be asleep...

318
00:18:24,340 --> 00:18:25,340
and ended up
actually falling asleep.

319
00:18:25,410 --> 00:18:29,580
The thought of having a kid like you
someday scares me. Seriously.

320
00:18:31,420 --> 00:18:32,420
Hey.

321
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:33,880
My brother's calling for me.

322
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:37,490
Here, a present for you.

323
00:18:39,690 --> 00:18:42,190
I picked out the best shots.
What do you think? Do you like them?

324
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:46,800
You printed these out? Thank you.

325
00:18:47,330 --> 00:18:49,030
I have nowhere to put these.

326
00:18:49,330 --> 00:18:51,000
Hey, be careful.

327
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,140
Don't get caught
leaving them around.

328
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,640
Just stick them in your bag, okay?

329
00:18:54,910 --> 00:18:57,410
Nice. You look beautiful, babe.

330
00:19:00,780 --> 00:19:04,180
- Settle down. We're at the office.
- No.

331
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:07,220
This is why you went public,
so don't hold back in front of me.

332
00:19:08,490 --> 00:19:12,390
Smiling works your cheek muscles,
giving you a more youthful face.

333
00:19:12,590 --> 00:19:13,920
A natural facelift, you could say.

334
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:15,430
Unbelievable.

335
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:17,290
By the way, Vice President...

336
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:20,560
You didn't call me all the way here
just for this, did you?

337
00:19:20,930 --> 00:19:22,000
Right.

338
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:25,370
Besides Mr. Park and Ms. Gong's
"Project Breakup,"

339
00:19:25,870 --> 00:19:28,710
I have an idea to help you two
move things forward.

340
00:19:29,540 --> 00:19:30,910
Don't you have
any actual work to do?

341
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:32,410
This is company business.

342
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:35,480
It's critical we get Pacu Nacho
to commit to the company.

343
00:19:35,610 --> 00:19:37,050
Hey, I told you I'd sign
a long-term contract.

344
00:19:37,380 --> 00:19:40,380
Contracts are made to be broken.
I can't trust that.

345
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:42,890
So, what's this brilliant idea,
Vice President?

346
00:19:43,890 --> 00:19:45,090
Let's secure some allies.

347
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:49,590
Allies who will be on your side
when your relationship goes public.

348
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:56,000
Oh, I have my grandma,
and she's always on my side.

349
00:19:56,370 --> 00:19:58,340
For me... Maybe Eun Bin?

350
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:01,710
- I don't think she'd be much help.
- Right?

351
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:04,710
Then maybe my grandfather's
a better bet?

352
00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:09,750
- Oh, yes.
- Yes. So work on your grandfather.

353
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:13,750
Hey, "work" on him? That's not how
you win someone's heart. Got it?

354
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:15,950
You have to approach them
with sincerity.

355
00:20:16,020 --> 00:20:17,090
Also,

356
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:19,890
this is my area of expertise.
Just leave it to me.

357
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:21,220
Yes.

358
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:29,030
It looks like you select
your own medicinal herbs, sir.

359
00:20:29,370 --> 00:20:31,700
Of course. I'm very selective.

360
00:20:35,170 --> 00:20:36,940
High-quality.

361
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:43,780
I only select high-quality,
domestic medicinal herbs.

362
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:46,480
- Get more shots of the herbs.
- Okay, got it.

363
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:59,660
Do you usually give your wife
acupuncture treatments like this?

364
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:04,170
Yes, my wife is
my greatest clinical success story.

365
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:07,840
So, do you also use acupuncture
for cosmetic treatments?

366
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:12,910
That's right. Medicinal cosmetology
is a rising star in K-beauty.

367
00:21:14,180 --> 00:21:16,780
No chemicals, no surgery.

368
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:23,790
My husband's dream is to share
Korean medicine with the world.

369
00:21:24,620 --> 00:21:25,620
I see.

370
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:29,990
And the reason my skin is so radiant
is all thanks to my husband.

371
00:21:30,230 --> 00:21:32,360
For three years in a row at the
Korean Medicine Doctors' Conference!

372
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,030
For three years in a row!

373
00:21:34,130 --> 00:21:36,400
He earned
the title of "Golden Hands."

374
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:39,240
You could call it
his "acupuncture of love."

375
00:21:39,870 --> 00:21:41,370
Golden hands of love.

376
00:21:42,310 --> 00:21:43,910
Come to
Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic.

377
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:44,910
Please come!

378
00:21:44,910 --> 00:21:47,380
We'll give you
a little poke of love!

379
00:21:49,580 --> 00:21:51,380
Hello. Yes, I'm Gong Dae Han.

380
00:21:52,650 --> 00:21:54,020
I don't know what to say.

381
00:21:56,020 --> 00:21:57,920
You scared me!
Gosh, you startled me!

382
00:21:58,460 --> 00:21:59,590
How do I look?

383
00:21:59,890 --> 00:22:02,860
Gosh, hey.
Aren't you going to change back?

384
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:06,760
- Why? Do I look like I've lost it?
- You know you do.

385
00:22:06,830 --> 00:22:09,970
I just thought I might get a date
if I'm on TV.

386
00:22:10,030 --> 00:22:11,470
So I really tried to look my best.

387
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:15,040
You're prettier without it.
Now, pull yourself together.

388
00:22:15,110 --> 00:22:16,810
We'll start in ten minutes...

389
00:22:18,110 --> 00:22:19,840
- We'll start in ten minutes.
- Okay.

390
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:23,010
Just act naturally.
Pretend the cameras aren't here.

391
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:24,950
Just relax and be yourselves.

392
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:29,620
- Okay.
- Easier said than done. Oh, man.

393
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:32,960
Let's begin. And action!

394
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:38,560
- Oh, boy.
- My, why carry something so heavy?

395
00:22:39,330 --> 00:22:42,800
Some fresh spring cabbage kimchi.
It's nice and crunchy.

396
00:22:43,170 --> 00:22:45,000
It's very delicious.

397
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:48,540
You brought
a ton of braised soybeans...

398
00:22:48,540 --> 00:22:50,910
and anchovies last time too.

399
00:22:50,970 --> 00:22:53,040
- Oh, my.
- Ms. Lee.

400
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:55,350
We appreciate you coming
all this way.

401
00:22:55,610 --> 00:22:58,580
Today, as we discussed,
you'll be receiving manual therapy.

402
00:22:59,950 --> 00:23:02,790
Excuse me, Mr. Gong.
Just be natural. Like usual.

403
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:04,720
Hey. Are you a robot?

404
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:07,220
Why are you so stiff?
Just be natural.

405
00:23:07,390 --> 00:23:10,890
Excuse me. I'm sorry, but...

406
00:23:11,260 --> 00:23:14,100
- I need something to calm me down.
- For crying out loud...

407
00:23:14,930 --> 00:23:16,300
Let's take a five-minute break.

408
00:23:16,370 --> 00:23:19,540
Yes, I'm so sorry, everyone.
Good grief.

409
00:23:21,170 --> 00:23:23,740
By any chance,
is Dr. Han not coming to the clinic?

410
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:26,980
No, but she'll join the shoot
at our home. Why do you ask?

411
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:31,650
In Dr. Yang's segments, his wife
often appears to show support.

412
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:33,050
Really?

413
00:23:33,580 --> 00:23:35,590
In that case,
I'll talk to her about it.

414
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:38,290
- Great, if you could talk to her...
- Yes, of course.

415
00:23:42,890 --> 00:23:43,890
Yes?

416
00:23:47,330 --> 00:23:50,700
I'm busy right now.
Let's talk when I get home.

417
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,400
You haven't told Jeong Han?

418
00:23:54,910 --> 00:23:58,210
Not yet.
It could still be a benign lesion.

419
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:04,080
Let's check the shape and margin
of the nodule on the ultrasound,

420
00:24:04,210 --> 00:24:07,020
and if it looks suspicious,
we'll do a biopsy right away.

421
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:13,120
- I'm nervous.
- I know.

422
00:24:13,890 --> 00:24:15,660
It's the family history
I'm worried about.

423
00:24:16,530 --> 00:24:18,200
Your parents...

424
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,030
They both passed away
from cancer, right?

425
00:24:21,830 --> 00:24:22,830
Yes.

426
00:24:24,730 --> 00:24:25,740
Let's go.

427
00:24:29,410 --> 00:24:31,780
My dear Endorphin,
did you get to work okay?

428
00:24:32,610 --> 00:24:36,310
- "My dear Endorphin."
- Gosh, you scared me.

429
00:24:36,780 --> 00:24:38,650
Could you not sneak up on me
like that?

430
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:43,350
You said you'd never date in secret.
Did you change your mind that fast?

431
00:24:43,490 --> 00:24:47,960
It just ended up that way.
All thanks to Officer Jung.

432
00:24:49,830 --> 00:24:52,660
I have no idea
why you're bringing him up.

433
00:24:53,330 --> 00:24:54,330
Nurse Oh.

434
00:24:54,730 --> 00:24:57,800
He isn't seeing another woman.
It was all a misunderstanding.

435
00:24:58,570 --> 00:24:59,870
You actually asked him that?

436
00:24:59,940 --> 00:25:02,910
Yes. He said he likes you,

437
00:25:02,970 --> 00:25:05,840
but he said he had to turn you down
for personal reasons.

438
00:25:06,140 --> 00:25:09,680
It's personal, so I can't tell you.
You should ask him yourself.

439
00:25:09,980 --> 00:25:14,380
Gosh, forget it.
Either he's into me, or he's not.

440
00:25:14,820 --> 00:25:16,090
So then...

441
00:25:16,590 --> 00:25:17,890
Are you open
to going on a blind date?

442
00:25:18,090 --> 00:25:19,190
Sure.

443
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:23,690
- Why? You want to set me up?
- Yes. I know a really handsome guy.

444
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:24,860
Nice!

445
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:26,360
Yes, ma'am!

446
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:35,510
Vice President.

447
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,570
Are you ready?

448
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:44,710
Pacu Nacho is going to have a fit
when he sees me at a stage check.

449
00:25:44,810 --> 00:25:47,380
So what? You're the Vice President.

450
00:25:48,290 --> 00:25:51,020
My own personal hype man. I like it.

451
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:55,890
Should we stream this fashion show
on YouTube?

452
00:25:56,190 --> 00:25:57,190
Great idea.

453
00:25:57,490 --> 00:26:00,660
A great way to share our brand story
directly with the public.

454
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:04,170
I just thought it would be good
for the Chairman to see it, too.

455
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:08,310
That's very thoughtful of you.

456
00:26:10,210 --> 00:26:11,310
Let's go.

457
00:26:11,610 --> 00:26:13,810
- You drive, Mr. Park.
- Okay.

458
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:22,020
This venue is bigger
than I expected.

459
00:26:23,090 --> 00:26:26,990
Marketing worked hard to find
a quality venue that fit the budget.

460
00:26:27,820 --> 00:26:30,890
Why? Are you checking up on us
to see if we blew the budget?

461
00:26:31,230 --> 00:26:33,200
That's part of it. And...

462
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:35,030
Tell me
when the guest list is ready.

463
00:26:35,270 --> 00:26:36,370
Got it.

464
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:42,570
- Dr. Han will be here soon, right?
- Yes. Hey, do a good job.

465
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:44,070
And don't go over the top.

466
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:45,680
Come on.

467
00:26:48,850 --> 00:26:49,950
She's here.

468
00:26:50,350 --> 00:26:52,250
- Dr. Han, you made it.
- Yes.

469
00:26:53,550 --> 00:26:54,990
The Vice President is here as well.

470
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:59,290
Wow, this venue is much bigger
than I expected.

471
00:26:59,460 --> 00:27:01,560
Thank you for coming all this way
after work.

472
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:06,330
You made it.

473
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:08,670
Yes. So...

474
00:27:08,670 --> 00:27:12,240
I'm going to go check on things
backstage.

475
00:27:17,410 --> 00:27:18,640
This way, please.

476
00:27:21,980 --> 00:27:24,810
Since this is your first runway,
you should get acclimated quickly.

477
00:27:25,380 --> 00:27:27,350
What's going on?
I thought you two made up.

478
00:27:27,850 --> 00:27:30,820
For now, please focus on preparing
for the show, Dr. Han.

479
00:27:31,390 --> 00:27:33,520
You let out the samples enough,
right?

480
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:36,860
They're being altered,
but don't eat whatever you want now.

481
00:27:36,930 --> 00:27:38,400
Gaining weight
will affect your walk,

482
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:39,860
and the clothes
won't look as good on you.

483
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:43,730
You need to practice your walk
during your downtime at the clinic.

484
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:47,070
And why is your skin so dull?
Gosh, seriously.

485
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:50,010
I'm going to book you a facial,
so make sure you go.

486
00:27:50,370 --> 00:27:52,540
Like I have time to go to a spa.

487
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:56,650
Gosh, just go.
You always need the last word.

488
00:27:56,650 --> 00:27:58,550
- What?
- Why are you so...

489
00:27:59,050 --> 00:28:00,050
Then...

490
00:28:01,420 --> 00:28:03,750
What? Why are you smiling?
That's creepy.

491
00:28:04,820 --> 00:28:07,390
I'm just jealous.
A mother and daughter like that.

492
00:28:09,290 --> 00:28:12,360
What? Did you expect a small event?
My gosh.

493
00:28:19,770 --> 00:28:21,400
You worked hard today, Dr. Han.

494
00:28:22,670 --> 00:28:24,710
By the way,
I don't see Mr. Park around.

495
00:28:25,710 --> 00:28:27,980
It looks like he was called
into a last-minute dinner meeting.

496
00:28:28,340 --> 00:28:29,680
I see.

497
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:31,510
Get home safe.

498
00:28:31,950 --> 00:28:34,620
- Aren't you coming with me?
- I have to stop by the sample room.

499
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,550
Darn, I was going to make you drive.

500
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:40,360
Dr. Han, you look tired.
Would you like a ride home?

501
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:42,160
Why?

502
00:28:42,860 --> 00:28:44,430
I'm heading to my parents' house
anyway.

503
00:28:44,690 --> 00:28:46,730
No, thank you.
What would I do about my car?

504
00:28:47,530 --> 00:28:48,530
I'm leaving.

505
00:28:51,670 --> 00:28:53,840
Why does she have to be so blunt
and make things awkward?

506
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:58,240
- My gosh.
- Babe, try to be nicer to Dr. Han.

507
00:28:58,510 --> 00:29:01,040
How am I supposed to be nice
when she's so rude to me?

508
00:29:09,820 --> 00:29:11,250
(Yu Jin)

509
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,430
Hey, Yu Jin.

510
00:29:19,360 --> 00:29:20,460
Really?

511
00:29:23,370 --> 00:29:26,400
Got it. Okay.

512
00:29:42,990 --> 00:29:46,020
- Volunteer work...
- You're home.

513
00:29:46,020 --> 00:29:48,960
Hey! Gosh, what took you so long?

514
00:29:49,030 --> 00:29:52,000
I was just checking the stage
for the fashion show.

515
00:29:54,030 --> 00:29:57,970
Have you considered the extra shoot
for "Human Theater?"

516
00:29:58,500 --> 00:30:01,470
Wasn't filming at our house enough?
Why are you asking me to do more?

517
00:30:01,740 --> 00:30:05,440
Listen, Bucket's wife
followed him around all day,

518
00:30:05,510 --> 00:30:08,040
and they got tons of footage of her
being a supportive wife. See?

519
00:30:08,380 --> 00:30:10,050
Can you imagine the comparisons?

520
00:30:10,410 --> 00:30:13,450
And you know how much you hate
being compared to others.

521
00:30:14,220 --> 00:30:16,090
So what do you want me to do?

522
00:30:16,890 --> 00:30:17,920
So, here's my idea.

523
00:30:18,250 --> 00:30:22,430
Let's host a health seminar
for the merchants at Onjeong Market.

524
00:30:22,630 --> 00:30:25,930
I'll handle physical health.
You can cover mental health. Right?

525
00:30:26,130 --> 00:30:27,700
How about a little collaboration?

526
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:31,170
That could work.

527
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:36,070
Thank you, Seong Mi! Really!
I've got to call the producer now!

528
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:38,980
In your face, Bucket! Yes!

529
00:30:49,150 --> 00:30:52,020
- Grandma, come on.
- This girl.

530
00:30:52,390 --> 00:30:54,490
I thought you said
you were swamped and exhausted.

531
00:30:54,490 --> 00:30:56,290
Why are you dragging me out
to exercise?

532
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:58,290
That's why I need to
work on my stamina!

533
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:00,930
I'm busy. The film crew
is coming over tonight.

534
00:31:00,930 --> 00:31:04,170
I have to clean and make food.
I have a million things to do.

535
00:31:04,470 --> 00:31:07,500
Come on, I'll help when we're done.
Let's go for a quick workout.

536
00:31:07,740 --> 00:31:10,170
- Here, put this on. Hurry.
- What has gotten into you?

537
00:31:10,540 --> 00:31:11,540
Unbelievable.

538
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:25,220
Wow, I'd only heard good things
about this place,

539
00:31:25,620 --> 00:31:27,020
but it's really beautiful.

540
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:31,630
- See? Aren't you glad you came out?
- I am. It's a breath of fresh air.

541
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:35,030
Oh, it's so nice here.

542
00:31:35,870 --> 00:31:39,700
- Isn't it nice here, Grandpa?
- It is. Spring is here.

543
00:31:47,610 --> 00:31:49,510
Oh, Director Yang is here.

544
00:31:50,180 --> 00:31:51,950
- Director!
- Wait, Ms. Gong?

545
00:31:54,980 --> 00:31:58,620
Wow, what a surprise
seeing you here! Hello.

546
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,990
- Hello.
- Fancy seeing you here, sir.

547
00:32:01,020 --> 00:32:02,360
It is, isn't it?

548
00:32:02,690 --> 00:32:05,900
For some reason, my grandson here
was pestering me to go for a walk.

549
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:07,100
Hello, Ms. Na.

550
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:09,170
Hello.

551
00:32:09,530 --> 00:32:10,630
Hey, Ms. Gong.

552
00:32:10,930 --> 00:32:12,370
How did you find out
about this place?

553
00:32:12,570 --> 00:32:15,640
Everyone kept saying
how nice it was.

554
00:32:15,710 --> 00:32:19,510
I see. I actually did some research
on the trails here.

555
00:32:19,910 --> 00:32:24,080
I can show you around, if you like.
Care to join us for a walk?

556
00:32:24,310 --> 00:32:25,320
Oh, my.

557
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:29,690
That would be amazing. Thank you.
Right, Grandma?

558
00:32:31,350 --> 00:32:32,360
Sure.

559
00:32:33,890 --> 00:32:36,590
All right, Grandpa, let's go.
Yes, this way. Right this way.

560
00:32:37,130 --> 00:32:38,830
Wow, Grandma,
this is going to be fun.

561
00:32:39,830 --> 00:32:42,130
This place is gorgeous.

562
00:32:42,570 --> 00:32:44,970
What a magnificent waterfall.

563
00:32:45,300 --> 00:32:48,440
- How thorough.
- Ms. Na, let me...

564
00:32:49,670 --> 00:32:51,670
- Be careful.
- I'll help you, sir.

565
00:32:51,740 --> 00:32:53,140
Okay, thank you.

566
00:32:53,940 --> 00:32:55,650
Director, could you take
a picture of me here?

567
00:32:55,710 --> 00:32:57,250
Okay. Here we go.

568
00:33:01,850 --> 00:33:03,490
You look so pretty, Grandma.

569
00:33:04,250 --> 00:33:06,260
How can you be so lovely?

570
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:11,930
- You're so pretty.
- Okay, I'll take it now.

571
00:33:12,030 --> 00:33:13,530
Oh, great!

572
00:33:14,230 --> 00:33:15,230
Grandma.

573
00:33:15,700 --> 00:33:18,430
Okay. All right,
taking the picture now.

574
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:25,880
I hope this isn't out of line,
but you're very beautiful, Ms. Na.

575
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:29,880
- I shouldn't have sat next to you.
- Oh, stop it.

576
00:33:29,950 --> 00:33:32,250
She's been famous for her beauty
since she was young.

577
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:35,320
Sir, you're talking
about ancient history.

578
00:33:35,390 --> 00:33:38,820
No, you haven't changed a bit.
You look exactly the same...

579
00:33:38,890 --> 00:33:41,520
as before I went to study abroad.
I was so surprised.

580
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:44,530
Stop it, you guys. That's enough.

581
00:33:46,300 --> 00:33:50,330
Wait. Director, you should go take
a picture with your grandpa, too.

582
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:52,030
- Okay.
- No, that's okay.

583
00:33:52,770 --> 00:33:53,970
A picture of me at my age? Why?

584
00:33:54,270 --> 00:33:55,470
Why take a photo of me
looking like this?

585
00:33:55,970 --> 00:33:58,710
Sir, for the rest of your life,

586
00:33:58,780 --> 00:34:00,780
today is the youngest
you'll ever be.

587
00:34:01,780 --> 00:34:02,780
Right.

588
00:34:03,310 --> 00:34:04,380
When you put it that way,
you have a point.

589
00:34:05,950 --> 00:34:08,950
- All right, then.
- Come on, Grandpa.

590
00:34:09,150 --> 00:34:10,790
Let's take a picture together.
It's been a while.

591
00:34:17,130 --> 00:34:19,400
Your smile is so pretty.

592
00:34:20,100 --> 00:34:22,500
Grandma, I bet a picture here
would look so beautiful.

593
00:34:23,370 --> 00:34:24,370
Just one more.

594
00:34:26,070 --> 00:34:27,070
By any chance,

595
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:29,910
that person you met in Seongdam
the other day...

596
00:34:30,270 --> 00:34:31,440
Have you heard from her?

597
00:34:32,280 --> 00:34:35,850
Actually, I was planning
to contact her tomorrow.

598
00:34:37,510 --> 00:34:39,220
When you speak with her,
could you please let me know?

599
00:34:39,650 --> 00:34:40,650
I will.

600
00:34:44,020 --> 00:34:45,660
Is this the same person?

601
00:34:47,090 --> 00:34:48,090
What?

602
00:34:55,230 --> 00:34:58,630
It's nice coming to places like this
with the grandkids.

603
00:34:58,730 --> 00:34:59,740
Yes, it really is.

604
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:01,700
This is my first time
at a place like this, too.

605
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,710
I'll bring you here often, Grandpa.

606
00:35:04,010 --> 00:35:07,740
Sir, would you like to try
gorgonzola pizza?

607
00:35:08,010 --> 00:35:09,980
- Gorgon, what?
- Oh, pardon?

608
00:35:10,480 --> 00:35:12,750
It's a cheese pizza
that you dip in honey.

609
00:35:12,750 --> 00:35:15,120
It's savory and light.
I think you'll really like it.

610
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:16,550
Really?

611
00:35:18,150 --> 00:35:19,160
You see, about...

612
00:35:20,490 --> 00:35:22,930
I'm sorry about
what happened the other day.

613
00:35:23,390 --> 00:35:26,030
No, it's okay. I'm really fine,

614
00:35:26,100 --> 00:35:27,900
so please don't worry about it.

615
00:35:29,170 --> 00:35:32,840
That's right, sir.
You already apologized last time.

616
00:35:33,270 --> 00:35:36,240
Thank you for your understanding,
Ms. Na.

617
00:35:37,310 --> 00:35:39,640
I heard you went to persuade
Dr. Han Seong Mi...

618
00:35:40,110 --> 00:35:43,280
so both doctors
could be on the show.

619
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:47,820
It wasn't persuasion. Just a favor.
I'm sorry for being so forward.

620
00:35:48,220 --> 00:35:49,950
Nonsense.
You have nothing to be sorry for.

621
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,890
Your grandson
has become a fine man, sir.

622
00:35:55,530 --> 00:35:58,260
He's certainly different
from his father.

623
00:36:01,660 --> 00:36:02,700
That was just a joke.

624
00:36:04,430 --> 00:36:05,430
Right.

625
00:36:19,720 --> 00:36:21,420
Okay, hold on a second.

626
00:36:22,220 --> 00:36:24,620
So, earlier, Dr. Han and Ms. Na...

627
00:36:24,690 --> 00:36:27,360
were both natural at the table,
which was great.

628
00:36:27,990 --> 00:36:31,430
For the rest of you,
please try to ignore the camera.

629
00:36:31,530 --> 00:36:33,160
Just relax and eat
like you normally would.

630
00:36:34,130 --> 00:36:37,330
- Dr. Han, could you guide them?
- Right.

631
00:36:37,330 --> 00:36:40,440
- Okay, I'll try.
- Yes, okay, great.

632
00:36:41,100 --> 00:36:42,570
- You can do it, right?
- Yes.

633
00:36:42,570 --> 00:36:43,870
- Right?
- Yes.

634
00:36:43,940 --> 00:36:47,110
Good grief, they're like robots.
They clam up as soon as they speak.

635
00:36:47,180 --> 00:36:49,680
- Unbelievable.
- I'll try.

636
00:36:50,550 --> 00:36:51,580
I just have to do it.

637
00:36:52,150 --> 00:36:53,950
- Just settle down for a second.
- Okay.

638
00:36:54,180 --> 00:36:56,720
- Okay, let's take it from the top!
- Right.

639
00:36:58,690 --> 00:37:02,090
Mother, these vegetable side dishes
are all so delicious today.

640
00:37:02,290 --> 00:37:06,900
Yes, seasonal spring greens are good
for immunity, so eat up, everyone.

641
00:37:06,900 --> 00:37:09,400
Yes. Especially our Woo Jae, right?

642
00:37:09,470 --> 00:37:12,770
You have to stay healthy.
Here, eat up. Eat a lot. Go on, eat.

643
00:37:12,970 --> 00:37:15,470
That's right. Yes, our Woo Jae.

644
00:37:16,070 --> 00:37:17,140
Hey, you need to eat up.

645
00:37:18,140 --> 00:37:21,910
Okay. Yes, Uncle, you eat too.

646
00:37:21,910 --> 00:37:23,280
- Yes.
- Yes, eat... Eat up.

647
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:24,910
For crying out loud.

648
00:37:25,250 --> 00:37:26,950
Excuse me.

649
00:37:27,450 --> 00:37:30,690
Can't I just eat?
This is seriously so hard.

650
00:37:31,650 --> 00:37:33,290
Seriously, I'm terrible at this.

651
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:36,690
We have a robot in our family.
A robot.

652
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,890
Oh, man.
We have a robot in our family.

653
00:37:39,300 --> 00:37:41,700
I think they're pretty much done
filming here.

654
00:37:42,330 --> 00:37:44,270
It looks like they're heading over
to your place next.

655
00:37:45,030 --> 00:37:48,840
Right!
Did your grandfather mention me?

656
00:37:49,770 --> 00:37:50,870
Of course, he did.

657
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:54,640
He said you were poised and sweet,
which is rare these days.

658
00:37:56,480 --> 00:37:59,550
Right. Yes, got it. Okay.

659
00:38:00,220 --> 00:38:01,250
See you tomorrow.

660
00:38:03,650 --> 00:38:05,190
Hey. What are you up to?

661
00:38:06,020 --> 00:38:07,420
What do you think? It's for my vlog.

662
00:38:07,790 --> 00:38:09,630
Isn't this the perfect chance
to boost my views?

663
00:38:11,130 --> 00:38:13,130
Are they still filming
over at Woo Jae's?

664
00:38:13,300 --> 00:38:16,600
No, they're finished.
The film crew is on their way here.

665
00:38:17,030 --> 00:38:18,870
How do you know that?

666
00:38:20,370 --> 00:38:22,570
What? Well...

667
00:38:23,910 --> 00:38:27,540
You could've said Ju Ah told you.
No need to get all flustered.

668
00:38:27,610 --> 00:38:30,210
My gosh. You're secretly dating her,
aren't you?

669
00:38:31,050 --> 00:38:34,050
- What?
- Our families are sworn enemies,

670
00:38:34,180 --> 00:38:37,390
and Mom's trying to set you up
with your company's vice president.

671
00:38:37,450 --> 00:38:40,560
So you're secretly dating
so the adults won't find out, right?

672
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:42,560
It's just...

673
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:47,160
Look at the great Yang Hyun Bin,
speechless for once.

674
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:52,200
Will he lie,
or will he tell the truth?

675
00:38:52,500 --> 00:38:57,270
Look at his face, torn by conflict.
Just look at him.

676
00:38:57,910 --> 00:39:00,280
Hey. Keep this a secret
from the rest of the family.

677
00:39:00,510 --> 00:39:02,210
What's in it for me?

678
00:39:03,250 --> 00:39:08,020
- How much do you want?
- We can still be double in-laws!

679
00:39:08,580 --> 00:39:11,350
But you have to promise
to keep this a secret.

680
00:39:11,590 --> 00:39:13,590
We're in trouble if they find out.
Got it?

681
00:39:14,620 --> 00:39:15,890
We'll see how you behave.

682
00:39:23,430 --> 00:39:26,870
- Is it over? Has the crew left?
- Yes.

683
00:39:28,040 --> 00:39:32,140
This is so unfair.
Why weren't you on camera?

684
00:39:32,210 --> 00:39:33,310
What?
Are you not part of the family?

685
00:39:33,710 --> 00:39:37,380
I told you I don't want my coworkers
knowing Dr. Han Seong Mi is my mom.

686
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:41,520
Why not?
You should be proud of our mom.

687
00:39:42,220 --> 00:39:45,820
Hey, I'm Gong Ju Ah, not only
Dr. Han Seong Mi's daughter.

688
00:39:45,890 --> 00:39:47,520
I'm my own person.

689
00:39:47,590 --> 00:39:50,830
You're both. What are you saying?
Of course, you're Mom's daughter.

690
00:39:50,890 --> 00:39:52,430
You're so pretentious.

691
00:39:52,860 --> 00:39:55,400
What was that? Looking for a fight?
It's been a while.

692
00:39:56,370 --> 00:39:59,140
I just got paid.
But since you're not family,

693
00:39:59,670 --> 00:40:00,700
I'm not getting you anything.

694
00:40:00,870 --> 00:40:04,710
Is that how you talk to your sister?
You're asking for trouble, right?

695
00:40:06,810 --> 00:40:07,810
Seriously!

696
00:40:08,740 --> 00:40:10,010
Why has he been
so irritating lately?

697
00:40:11,650 --> 00:40:12,650
Unbelievable!

698
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:16,220
Hello, everyone!
Welcome to Sunny TV!

699
00:40:16,290 --> 00:40:18,020
It's your girl, Yanggaeng.

700
00:40:18,350 --> 00:40:22,690
Today, for a special episode,
I'm on the set of "Human Theater."

701
00:40:25,290 --> 00:40:26,460
This is the director.

702
00:40:27,300 --> 00:40:28,730
And the director of photography.

703
00:40:29,570 --> 00:40:33,870
They're getting ready to film now.
Come on, say hi!

704
00:40:34,240 --> 00:40:36,040
- Hi.
- Hi.

705
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:39,110
You guys over here, say hi.

706
00:40:39,540 --> 00:40:40,540
Hi.

707
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:43,910
Nice to meet you all.
Please take good care of my family.

708
00:40:44,050 --> 00:40:45,050
- Of course.
- Of course.

709
00:40:47,380 --> 00:40:48,420
Ta-da!

710
00:40:49,020 --> 00:40:51,820
And the star of today's show is
none other than...

711
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:56,690
Ta-da! And the star of today's show
is none other than...

712
00:40:58,630 --> 00:40:59,630
So, how do we look?

713
00:40:59,900 --> 00:41:02,400
Mom, I told you not to wear
that outfit.

714
00:41:02,430 --> 00:41:05,430
And Dad, that tie looks like
it's choking you.

715
00:41:05,570 --> 00:41:06,940
The nerve of this kid.

716
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:09,870
See? I told you
your outfit was a bit much.

717
00:41:09,970 --> 00:41:13,140
- You too.
- This whole spread is over the top.

718
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:15,680
Seriously, what is all this?

719
00:41:15,780 --> 00:41:18,080
Hey, that's enough.
Eun Bin, take your seat.

720
00:41:18,410 --> 00:41:21,350
Let's just do as our stepmom says,
Eun Bin.

721
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:25,860
Gosh, this is so embarrassing.
I can't believe this.

722
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,130
Let's start filming, shall we?

723
00:41:31,430 --> 00:41:32,430
Oh, well...

724
00:41:33,230 --> 00:41:34,900
Do you normally eat like this?

725
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:40,070
Yes, we always eat like this.
We plan a balanced menu every week,

726
00:41:40,240 --> 00:41:43,970
and use only organic ingredients
and all-natural seasonings.

727
00:41:45,240 --> 00:41:48,410
There's no better medicine
than nutritious food.

728
00:41:48,580 --> 00:41:49,850
Of course. That's absolutely right.

729
00:41:51,010 --> 00:41:54,480
And my wife here prepares
all of it herself.

730
00:41:57,950 --> 00:41:58,950
All right, guys.

731
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:01,120
Let's...

732
00:42:01,490 --> 00:42:02,490
Tomorrow?

733
00:42:03,660 --> 00:42:04,730
Tomorrow sounds great.

734
00:42:05,490 --> 00:42:07,330
Okay, I'll see you tomorrow then.

735
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:10,430
Yes. I can't wait.

736
00:42:11,570 --> 00:42:12,570
Hey!

737
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:14,240
You scared me.

738
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:17,270
Why so excited for tomorrow?
Who are you meeting?

739
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:19,740
Just a friend. Is the shoot over?

740
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:23,850
Yes, you can come down now.
Everyone's dying to feed you dinner.

741
00:42:24,380 --> 00:42:28,420
- I must be popular.
- I'm so jealous.

742
00:42:30,990 --> 00:42:33,020
- Mother.
- Yes?

743
00:42:36,030 --> 00:42:37,390
My gosh, what is it?

744
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:39,030
You're going to sleep in my room?

745
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:40,830
Is Jeong Han bothering you?

746
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:42,600
No.

747
00:42:42,930 --> 00:42:47,170
Everyone will sleep in tomorrow,
so if we want to sneak out quietly,

748
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:48,670
I thought it'd be best
if we slept in the same room.

749
00:42:48,740 --> 00:42:52,610
You're so thoughtful. Okay.
We haven't done this in a while.

750
00:42:53,510 --> 00:42:57,650
Oh, right, I went out for a walk
with Ju Ah this morning.

751
00:42:58,410 --> 00:43:01,150
We saw Dr. Yang from the clinic
and his grandson.

752
00:43:01,420 --> 00:43:03,920
- You did?
- Yes.

753
00:43:04,390 --> 00:43:06,160
I've thought this before, but...

754
00:43:06,690 --> 00:43:09,830
that grandson of his seems like
a very grounded person.

755
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:12,030
I suppose he is.

756
00:43:12,700 --> 00:43:16,400
- I can't believe he's Bucket's son.
- I know.

757
00:43:17,070 --> 00:43:19,570
We had a good laugh about that,
actually.

758
00:43:20,100 --> 00:43:22,300
But his son...

759
00:43:22,770 --> 00:43:25,940
He liked Ju Ah
when they were kids, right?

760
00:43:25,940 --> 00:43:26,980
Yes, he did.

761
00:43:28,040 --> 00:43:31,350
I could still see love in his eyes
when he looked at Ju Ah.

762
00:43:31,910 --> 00:43:34,850
Really? I couldn't really tell.

763
00:43:35,420 --> 00:43:37,220
He must get that from his father.

764
00:43:37,850 --> 00:43:40,320
- He can't get over his first love.
- My gosh.

765
00:43:42,190 --> 00:43:44,790
But of all the bad luck,
they work at the same company.

766
00:43:46,060 --> 00:43:48,330
So he must be heartbroken
that Ju Ah is with someone.

767
00:43:49,330 --> 00:43:52,000
I wonder how things are going
with the VP.

768
00:43:52,670 --> 00:43:55,740
Bucket's wife was using talismans
and everything.

769
00:43:56,310 --> 00:43:59,940
- Talismans?
- Yes. Gosh, she's the worst.

770
00:44:00,580 --> 00:44:04,710
Seriously, once this shoot is over,
I hope we never see them again.

771
00:44:06,050 --> 00:44:07,720
We didn't see each other
for one day,

772
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:12,120
and I miss you like crazy.

773
00:44:12,490 --> 00:44:15,690
Oh, my gosh.
What if someone hears you?

774
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:18,960
Hey, I'm alone in my room.
Who's going to hear me?

775
00:44:19,630 --> 00:44:24,130
Oh, Dorphini.
I have some homework for you.

776
00:44:24,230 --> 00:44:26,200
Think you can have it done
by our date tomorrow?

777
00:44:26,770 --> 00:44:28,500
Homework? What kind of homework?

778
00:44:29,710 --> 00:44:31,310
Make a bucket list
and bring it with you.

779
00:44:32,110 --> 00:44:33,440
If you write down everything
you want to do,

780
00:44:34,080 --> 00:44:35,310
I'll make all your wishes come true.

781
00:44:37,510 --> 00:44:41,480
- You have to write one too, okay?
- You got me.

782
00:44:41,980 --> 00:44:43,750
I didn't expect
to get homework, too.

783
00:44:45,320 --> 00:44:47,060
All right.
I'll think of what to write down.

784
00:44:47,620 --> 00:44:49,830
Sleep well.
I'll see you tomorrow, Dorphini.

785
00:44:50,730 --> 00:44:53,660
Okay. See you tomorrow, Tamin.

786
00:44:56,070 --> 00:44:58,800
- You scared me.
- Close the door when taking a call.

787
00:44:59,170 --> 00:45:02,040
Eun Bin is dying to find out
who your boyfriend is.

788
00:45:03,710 --> 00:45:05,070
Did you hear all that?

789
00:45:05,510 --> 00:45:07,640
Homework, bucket list, Tamin.

790
00:45:10,310 --> 00:45:14,380
Are you okay
with me dating Mr. Gong?

791
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:18,420
Yes, I looked into it.
There's nothing illegal about it.

792
00:45:30,600 --> 00:45:32,430
I could've gone by myself.

793
00:45:32,940 --> 00:45:36,170
Why do you go out of your way
for my grandma's death anniversary?

794
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:37,610
What are you talking about?

795
00:45:38,110 --> 00:45:41,980
She raised you well, so I care.
Of course, I should be here.

796
00:45:46,050 --> 00:45:47,350
It's Mi Hyang.

797
00:45:48,520 --> 00:45:49,650
Mi Hyang.

798
00:45:50,290 --> 00:45:53,320
I was just about to call you.
Thanks for reaching out.

799
00:45:54,420 --> 00:45:55,790
Yes, Ms. Na.

800
00:45:56,690 --> 00:46:01,360
For the last few days,
I've been looking high and low,

801
00:46:01,860 --> 00:46:05,470
and I even showed his picture
to everyone I could find.

802
00:46:06,070 --> 00:46:07,070
But...

803
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:12,110
no one said they saw anyone
who looked like Dr. Gong.

804
00:46:12,540 --> 00:46:14,710
I see.

805
00:46:16,010 --> 00:46:17,310
I was hoping, but I guess not.

806
00:46:18,010 --> 00:46:20,250
I'm so sorry to put you through
all that trouble for nothing.

807
00:46:21,250 --> 00:46:22,550
Thank you so much.

808
00:46:22,850 --> 00:46:26,160
And be sure to stop by
when you need a refill.

809
00:46:27,190 --> 00:46:29,360
All right. Take care.

810
00:46:33,560 --> 00:46:35,700
I guess you were mistaken.

811
00:46:36,530 --> 00:46:37,530
I guess so.

812
00:46:39,500 --> 00:46:40,500
Mother.

813
00:46:41,240 --> 00:46:44,740
If you're still disappointed,
we could look for him next weekend.

814
00:46:45,110 --> 00:46:46,110
I'm not.

815
00:46:47,410 --> 00:46:49,710
He's waiting.
I should give him a call.

816
00:46:53,480 --> 00:46:55,420
- Dad, the shoot...
- Yes, Ms. Na.

817
00:46:57,790 --> 00:46:59,120
Yes, right.

818
00:47:01,360 --> 00:47:02,360
I see.

819
00:47:03,430 --> 00:47:04,430
Is that right?

820
00:47:05,830 --> 00:47:07,900
I was hoping it might be true,
but I guess not.

821
00:47:10,370 --> 00:47:12,470
Thank you for calling. Goodbye.

822
00:47:14,700 --> 00:47:16,940
What were you talking
to Ms. Na about?

823
00:47:21,710 --> 00:47:24,450
Someone said they saw a man
who looked like Gi Cheol.

824
00:47:25,250 --> 00:47:27,720
What? Jeong Han's father?

825
00:47:27,980 --> 00:47:30,590
I thought he might be
with your mother,

826
00:47:31,290 --> 00:47:33,520
so I went with Ms. Na
to go look for them.

827
00:47:34,090 --> 00:47:35,090
And?

828
00:47:36,430 --> 00:47:37,690
It was a false alarm.

829
00:47:40,360 --> 00:47:41,360
Do you want to find Mom?

830
00:47:43,570 --> 00:47:45,030
If you do, just say the word.

831
00:47:46,540 --> 00:47:47,540
I can look for her.

832
00:47:48,440 --> 00:47:49,440
Forget it.

833
00:47:50,240 --> 00:47:51,910
Unless she decides to come back
on her own.

834
00:47:56,140 --> 00:47:57,880
(Onjeong Market)

835
00:48:01,150 --> 00:48:04,050
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

836
00:48:04,590 --> 00:48:07,390
Couldn't you have come earlier?
It's almost time to film.

837
00:48:10,230 --> 00:48:11,230
Did you hear?

838
00:48:12,130 --> 00:48:13,130
About what?

839
00:48:13,800 --> 00:48:15,230
Your mother and my father...

840
00:48:16,600 --> 00:48:17,970
They went to look for them.

841
00:48:19,570 --> 00:48:20,570
What do you mean, "them?"

842
00:48:21,240 --> 00:48:22,400
Your father and my mother.

843
00:48:23,410 --> 00:48:24,410
What?

844
00:48:25,510 --> 00:48:27,040
When? Where did they go?

845
00:48:27,580 --> 00:48:29,310
A few days ago, someone said
they saw a look-alike,

846
00:48:30,050 --> 00:48:31,910
so they went to Seongdam
to find them.

847
00:48:32,950 --> 00:48:34,380
Seongdam?

848
00:48:36,180 --> 00:48:39,320
- We're ready now. Please come out.
- Okay.

849
00:48:43,160 --> 00:48:44,160
They're starting to film.

850
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:47,360
Gong Jeong Han.

851
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:51,230
Yes, you go ahead.
I'll be right out.

852
00:49:00,680 --> 00:49:01,680
Eun Bin, where are you going?

853
00:49:01,740 --> 00:49:04,680
Mom has training at the head office,
so I'm tagging along.

854
00:49:04,880 --> 00:49:07,220
I'm going to wait and then bug her
to buy me some clothes.

855
00:49:08,050 --> 00:49:10,490
By the way,
you look super pretty today.

856
00:49:11,190 --> 00:49:12,720
- You think?
- Yes.

857
00:49:12,920 --> 00:49:16,220
You said you were meeting a friend.
That friend must be a guy.

858
00:49:16,220 --> 00:49:17,360
It's a secret.

859
00:49:19,490 --> 00:49:23,830
This is our main product line
for the store.

860
00:49:25,400 --> 00:49:29,070
- Each product has its own audience?
- That's right.

861
00:49:29,540 --> 00:49:32,510
I'll send the reference materials
for your consultations separately.

862
00:49:32,510 --> 00:49:34,010
Oh, sure.

863
00:49:34,080 --> 00:49:38,810
You'll update the materials
for new products, right?

864
00:49:39,010 --> 00:49:40,120
Of course.

865
00:49:47,860 --> 00:49:51,430
Woo Jae, want some strawberries?
Okay, here you go.

866
00:49:56,800 --> 00:50:00,140
When I see yummy food,
I think of Woo Jae.

867
00:50:02,770 --> 00:50:05,340
Gosh, what's taking Mom so long
with her training?

868
00:50:09,680 --> 00:50:10,780
Hold on, what?

869
00:50:11,650 --> 00:50:13,280
Am I seeing things?

870
00:50:15,080 --> 00:50:17,390
No, that's him. That's my Woo Jae.

871
00:50:17,920 --> 00:50:20,360
We must be soulmates. Woo Jae!

872
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:28,000
Hey...

873
00:50:29,200 --> 00:50:30,200
Woo Jae?

874
00:50:30,970 --> 00:50:32,270
So, did you find out?

875
00:50:32,330 --> 00:50:34,000
Yes. I think
we can go look over there.

876
00:50:34,340 --> 00:50:35,800
- Let's go.
- Okay.

877
00:50:41,080 --> 00:50:42,110
What the...

878
00:50:43,810 --> 00:50:44,810
Unbelievable.

879
00:50:48,080 --> 00:50:49,120
Here.

880
00:50:51,990 --> 00:50:53,020
What the heck?

881
00:50:53,690 --> 00:50:55,060
What are those two doing?

882
00:50:56,090 --> 00:50:57,130
It's pretty.

883
00:51:11,640 --> 00:51:14,180
Eun Bin, what do you think?
It's pretty, isn't it?

884
00:51:15,110 --> 00:51:16,110
Yes.

885
00:51:16,880 --> 00:51:18,180
Can I help you find something?

886
00:51:18,950 --> 00:51:20,380
What are your best sellers
right now?

887
00:51:20,820 --> 00:51:21,820
One moment.

888
00:51:24,650 --> 00:51:26,460
This style is very popular
right now.

889
00:51:26,720 --> 00:51:28,860
It's very light and perfect
for this time of year.

890
00:51:31,690 --> 00:51:34,500
What do you think of this, honey?
Should we get matching ones?

891
00:51:35,130 --> 00:51:36,130
Sure.

892
00:51:36,300 --> 00:51:37,370
Hey.

893
00:51:37,530 --> 00:51:40,440
You were so excited to buy clothes,
so why the long face?

894
00:51:40,800 --> 00:51:42,270
Is it because
I made you wait too long?

895
00:51:42,940 --> 00:51:47,240
No, I think I'm having a sugar crash
from the dessert I ate.

896
00:51:47,340 --> 00:51:49,210
- I'm so sleepy.
- You are?

897
00:51:49,780 --> 00:51:53,380
Okay, I'll pick something for you.
You have to wear whatever I choose.

898
00:51:56,150 --> 00:51:59,790
What would look pretty
on my Eun Bin?

899
00:52:03,960 --> 00:52:05,190
Mr. Gong, where are you?

900
00:52:07,300 --> 00:52:11,170
Oh, hey.
Shoot. I'm actually on a date.

901
00:52:15,140 --> 00:52:16,910
Just wait there.

902
00:52:17,410 --> 00:52:20,580
Your date will be there shortly.
Okay, bye.

903
00:52:22,240 --> 00:52:25,350
- You're here!
- Why are you so happy?

904
00:52:29,150 --> 00:52:32,090
What the heck?
How am I supposed to know who it is?

905
00:52:52,240 --> 00:52:54,710
You! Why are you here?

906
00:52:56,480 --> 00:53:00,220
Mr. Gong from the clinic
called me here for something urgent.

907
00:53:02,550 --> 00:53:03,690
You've got to be kidding me.

908
00:53:05,450 --> 00:53:06,520
Jin Ah.

909
00:53:08,860 --> 00:53:10,360
If you don't mind,

910
00:53:11,360 --> 00:53:12,660
would you like to talk for a bit?

911
00:53:18,530 --> 00:53:21,600
What was that all about?
Playing Cupid, are you?

912
00:53:22,170 --> 00:53:24,810
They like each other,
so it'd be great if it works out.

913
00:53:25,510 --> 00:53:26,540
Did you do your homework?

914
00:53:27,140 --> 00:53:28,740
Let me see the bucket list
you wrote down.

915
00:53:30,150 --> 00:53:31,210
I didn't get to it.

916
00:53:32,110 --> 00:53:34,450
- Why not?
- It was just too hard.

917
00:53:35,250 --> 00:53:38,250
What I like, what I want to do...

918
00:53:39,190 --> 00:53:41,290
I've never once thought
about things like that.

919
00:53:50,130 --> 00:53:52,470
Then let's figure it out together,
slowly.

920
00:53:54,000 --> 00:53:56,370
- Did you write one?
- Write what?

921
00:53:57,040 --> 00:53:58,110
There's only one thing on my list.

922
00:53:58,770 --> 00:53:59,770
What is it?

923
00:54:02,180 --> 00:54:04,380
There it is. My bucket list.

924
00:54:13,190 --> 00:54:14,420
Playing with Ji Hu.

925
00:54:15,560 --> 00:54:19,160
That's your one and only
bucket list item?

926
00:54:21,430 --> 00:54:22,430
Yes.

927
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:30,740
(The late Kim Sun Bok)

928
00:54:35,710 --> 00:54:36,710
Grandma.

929
00:54:39,450 --> 00:54:40,680
I'm here.

930
00:54:42,280 --> 00:54:44,290
Even after all this time,

931
00:54:45,520 --> 00:54:47,820
seeing your picture
still brings me to tears.

932
00:54:54,500 --> 00:54:56,500
Every year when I come here,

933
00:54:57,270 --> 00:54:59,600
I want to be able to face you
without any shame.

934
00:55:00,170 --> 00:55:03,370
And I try my best
to do right by Seong Mi,

935
00:55:05,470 --> 00:55:07,580
but I still worry it's not enough.

936
00:55:10,210 --> 00:55:11,210
Please...

937
00:55:11,750 --> 00:55:15,180
watch over our Seong Mi for us.

938
00:55:17,990 --> 00:55:20,520
For her parents
who passed away too soon,

939
00:55:20,960 --> 00:55:21,990
please make sure our Seong Mi...

940
00:55:22,660 --> 00:55:26,560
lives a long, happy,
and healthy life.

941
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:29,760
I'm truly begging you.

942
00:55:33,840 --> 00:55:34,870
Dear.

943
00:55:36,540 --> 00:55:39,310
You must be going through menopause.

944
00:55:40,110 --> 00:55:42,340
Why are you so weepy
all of a sudden?

945
00:55:46,610 --> 00:55:48,980
- What...
- What do I do, Mother?

946
00:55:51,190 --> 00:55:53,690
What do you mean?
What are you talking about?

947
00:55:59,430 --> 00:56:00,430
I...

948
00:56:02,130 --> 00:56:03,570
I have breast cancer.

949
00:56:05,500 --> 00:56:06,740
What did you say?

950
00:56:07,400 --> 00:56:09,300
No, what are you talking about?

951
00:56:10,140 --> 00:56:11,710
No, hey.

952
00:56:12,110 --> 00:56:14,780
No, Seong Mi,
what on earth are you saying?

953
00:56:15,980 --> 00:56:17,510
I'm sorry, Mother.

954
00:56:17,810 --> 00:56:18,810
This can't be.

955
00:56:19,550 --> 00:56:20,550
Honey.

956
00:56:23,890 --> 00:56:28,090
Mother, what do I do?

957
00:56:38,630 --> 00:56:39,800
For the clinic,

958
00:56:40,540 --> 00:56:42,940
I'm looking for someone
to cover for a few months.

959
00:56:45,740 --> 00:56:48,180
I've already spoken
to the network, too.

960
00:56:50,780 --> 00:56:52,950
I'll just keep working
until Ju Ah's fashion show.

961
00:56:54,350 --> 00:56:56,020
Then I'll have the surgery
and take time off to recover.

962
00:56:57,990 --> 00:57:00,690
You'll be okay
once you have the surgery, right?

963
00:57:03,590 --> 00:57:04,730
Yes.

964
00:57:05,990 --> 00:57:07,360
As for the rest of the family...

965
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:10,570
I'll tell them myself
when I'm ready.

966
00:57:15,100 --> 00:57:16,740
How could fate be so cruel?

967
00:57:28,820 --> 00:57:31,420
- We're home.
- Hey, Min Seo.

968
00:57:32,490 --> 00:57:34,190
What time should we study English
tomorrow?

969
00:57:34,360 --> 00:57:35,560
What time works for you?

970
00:57:35,620 --> 00:57:37,360
I'm free whenever.
Whatever's best for you.

971
00:57:37,830 --> 00:57:39,430
- How about around...
- What's going on?

972
00:57:40,060 --> 00:57:41,360
What are you two whispering about?

973
00:57:41,630 --> 00:57:45,130
What? It's nothing.
Min Seo, have you had dinner?

974
00:57:45,830 --> 00:57:48,100
- I was going to make something...
- No, I'll make you something.

975
00:57:59,880 --> 00:58:02,680
Seriously,
why do I have such a bad feeling?

976
00:58:06,220 --> 00:58:09,290
I have so many clothes I can't wear.
What was I thinking buying more?

977
00:58:09,360 --> 00:58:10,360
Unbelievable.

978
00:58:15,430 --> 00:58:16,430
Darn it!

979
00:58:16,970 --> 00:58:17,970
Seriously.

980
00:58:19,200 --> 00:58:20,370
What's this?

981
00:58:22,140 --> 00:58:24,540
It's all clothes I can't even wear.
Unbelievable.

982
00:58:27,540 --> 00:58:28,540
What's in here?

983
00:58:31,950 --> 00:58:32,950
Mom.

984
00:58:33,510 --> 00:58:36,450
Why did you put a bar of soap here?
It belongs in the bathroom.

985
00:58:36,520 --> 00:58:37,790
So annoying!

986
00:58:40,020 --> 00:58:41,020
What?

987
00:58:42,020 --> 00:58:43,560
This isn't soap.

988
00:58:54,200 --> 00:58:55,570
What are all these?

989
00:59:09,180 --> 00:59:11,120
I feel like
I've seen this picture before.

990
00:59:12,490 --> 00:59:14,660
Where could I have seen this?

991
01:00:11,180 --> 01:00:12,880
Looks like
it's just the three of us today.

992
01:00:13,210 --> 01:00:14,920
But what's
with the abalone porridge?

993
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:18,220
Your mom's exhausted.
This is to help her regain strength.

994
01:00:20,150 --> 01:00:21,860
I must have dozed off, Mother.

995
01:00:22,160 --> 01:00:24,930
Always so worn out, aren't you?

996
01:00:24,990 --> 01:00:28,000
Ju Ah. From now on,
you're driving to and from work.

997
01:00:28,360 --> 01:00:31,800
Grandma, it's okay, really.
I'd rather just take the bus.

998
01:00:31,870 --> 01:00:33,530
Just do as you're told.

999
01:00:33,840 --> 01:00:36,340
It's all right, Mother.
I can drive myself.

1000
01:00:37,070 --> 01:00:39,670
Didn't you hear me? Answer me!

1001
01:00:40,340 --> 01:00:42,680
Okay. Why are you getting so angry?

1002
01:00:44,680 --> 01:00:46,910
Here, this one's for Seong Mi.

1003
01:00:49,020 --> 01:00:51,620
No, Grandma, that's too much.
Mom's been gaining weight lately.

1004
01:00:51,690 --> 01:00:53,590
- None of her clothes fit...
- Gong Ju Ah!

1005
01:01:38,870 --> 01:01:40,100
Ju Ah? Are you in here?

1006
01:01:44,610 --> 01:01:45,970
Where did she go?

1007
01:01:51,950 --> 01:01:53,250
Honestly...

1008
01:02:11,000 --> 01:02:12,100
Wait a minute...

1009
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:14,440
Who in the world is this?

1010
01:02:51,110 --> 01:02:53,710
(Recipe For Love)

1011
01:02:54,110 --> 01:02:57,040
- One sundaeguk to go.
- Go check that lady's face.

1012
01:02:58,610 --> 01:03:02,920
The last thing I want is
for you to be unhappy because of me.

1013
01:03:02,980 --> 01:03:04,550
Are you confessing your feelings
or rejecting me?

1014
01:03:06,120 --> 01:03:10,320
I need you to break up with Ju Ah
before our families find out.

1015
01:03:10,360 --> 01:03:12,660
- I'll do my best.
- No.

1016
01:03:14,930 --> 01:03:17,200
Just you wait. I'm going to get
to the bottom of this.

1017
01:03:19,270 --> 01:03:21,240
Are you keeping
another secret from me?
